article.headline: Utah State 66, Weber State 60
article.story: OGDEN, Utah (AP) -- Nate Harris scored 12 points and pulled down nine rebounds to lead Utah State to a 66-60 victory over Weber State on Tuesday night. The Aggies (2-0) broke a 19-game home winning streak for the Wildcats (1-1) and ended Utah State's two-game losing streak in Ogden. Spencer Nelson added 13 points and eight rebounds and Mark Brown scored 11 points for Utah State. Slobodon Ocokoljic led Weber State with 22 points and 10 rebounds. Lance Allred added 15 points for the Wildcats. The teams were close much of the second half before the Aggies broke ahead on a 11-2 run with less than 10 minutes to go. In an effort to keep up, the Wildcats shot several 3-pointers, but hit nothing. Weber State finished the game with 19 percent (3-for-16) from behind the arc. Despite foul trouble and shooting 31 percent from the field, the Aggies took a 27-24 lead into halftime. Utah State made up for the poor shooting by making 10-of-12 from the free-throw line.
